 years of experience in developing embedded systems or mobile robots in the robotics, aviation, automotive, or higher-reliability operating environments.\", \"• Experience in developing communication interfaces(I2C, SPI, UART, CAN, etc.)\", \"• Proficient in C, C++, Python, shell scripts with a strong understanding of various programming languages\", \"• Proficient in computer architecture, embedded software, device drivers, operating systems, and Linux\", \"• Proactive and self-driven individual who thrives in a rapidly changing environment\", \"• Excellent problem-solving skills\", \"• Experience in controlling and implementing interfaces with motors, IMU sensors and camera modules\", \"• Proactive and self-driven individual who thrives in a rapidly changing environment\", \"• Excellent problem-solving skills\", \"• Intermediate or higher proficiency in English to collaborate with U.S. team\"]}',NULL,NULL,'2024-09-12 01:24:20',1),(95,222067,'{\"id\": 222067, \"title\": \"Lead Firmware Engineer (15년 이상)\", \"preferred\": [\"• M.S. or Ph.D. in electrical, electronics, computer science, or other engineering disciplines\", \"• Proficient with ROS and PX4 flight stack algorithms\", \"• Experience in the development of gimbal, ESC, flight controller, RC transmitters, and optical flow modules\", \"• Experience in field testing of mobile robots and aerial vehicles, specifically drones\", \"• Experience in the development of a custom micro flight control unit or extensive customization of the PX4 flight stack\", \"• Experience with flight testing with controller tuning for UAV platforms and post-flight analysis for control response improvements\", \"• Literacy of Linux firmware and Linux-based systems, manufacturing process, and field problems troubleshooting skills\"], \"work_info\": [\"• Develop embedded firmware with various MCUs and Application processors\", \"• Develop drone stations firmware with motors and sensors control\", \"• Develop a gimbal control firmware\", 