ion]\", \"This position will be responsible for leading software implementation of contracted projects, providing software delivery plan, technical customer interfacing for software issues, and coordination across software functional teams. The Software Project Technical Leader will also drive amplifier application software implementation estimation, production issue solution, including but not limited to embedded software design, implementation and verification. The candidate is required to work effectively with local automakers, flexible resource teams and other regional functional teams. Fluent speaking and writing skill in both English and native language is a must for this position.\"], \"qualifications\": [\"• RFI/RFQ - Support functional level software requirements (e.g. diagnostics and networking) analysis.\", \"• Planning - Schedule software FROP and release plan to customer.\", \"• Design – Prepare detail level software design and component configuration.\", \"• Implementation – Lead software specification development and resolve technical issues.\", \"• Verification – Fix software defects under the help from software testing and integration teams.\", \"• Delivery - Release software features to customer on schedule with quality.\", \"• Product Support - Serve as first line of defense for software related customer issues, such as 8D support.\", \"• Communication – Understand technical challenges in detail and be able to discuss with customer and other Bose engineering teams effectively.\", \"• Customer Orientation – Work closely with regional engineering teams to satisfy customer request.\", \"• Coordination – Coordinate with algorithm, platform and DQE to delivery software features. Coordinate with SE, EPM, PDM, HW and SIE to deliver AMP solution.\", \"• Process - Follow Bose software best practice and guide the team to exercise it.\", \"• Management - Provide software status and issue report and update to other engineering managers.\", \"[Experience]\", \